{
  "stem": "3022.5",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They strafed and they destroyed them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And miraculously, they were able to pick up-- the SS was out machine gun-- the SS guards were in the perimeter-- without hurting any of the prisoners.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "When we saw the planes on fire and the guards running, we ran.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They had mounds of potatoes and kohlrabies that they kept in the mounds for the winter.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We went over there, dug them out, pulled them out, and we-- and the burning planes among exploding.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Machine gun ammunitions, we begged them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And then we danced around the planes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Because this was a dance of defiance.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "That was for the first time we saw the beginning of the end for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Camp Ganacker, the conditions were very bad.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We lived in hovels, dug out into the ground.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And the place where we slept was a little bit elevated from the ground.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The few stalls, and that's where we slept.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It was wet and cold all the time over there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The guards were very vicious.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I know that in the mornings after the rain, when the dew was in the field, some of the French prisoners from Luxembourg used to jump out from the line.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "They were looking for snails.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And the guards-- when they used to bend down-- they used to aim at their testicles.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And they'd shoot them just out for fun, just out of pure viciousness.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "On April 23, in the middle of the night, we were awakened.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We were told to assemble, told to take our blankets.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And we were being taken to an unknown destination.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Weeks before that, we could hear the American planes bombing the adjacent cities, the ground heaving.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "The Americans flew during the day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And at night, the British used to come and bomb.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
